  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Through FY2026 to date federal contract obligations total $456B. Obligations are led by Texas with $69.1B, followed by Virginia with $64.2B and California with $38.6B. Other states in the top ten include Maryland at $22.5B, Arizona at $20.9B, District Of Columbia at $19.2B, Florida at $18.5B, Pennsylvania at $17.8B, Connecticut at $14.5B, and New Mexico at $13.1B. These figures report federal contract obligations by state for the period FY2026 to date and note that total award value figures are full contract values, not single-year obligations.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "?Which states lead federal contract obligations?",
        "body": "Texas leads federal contract obligations with $69.1B. Virginia is second with $64.2B and California is third with $38.6B. Maryland, Arizona, and District Of Columbia follow with $22.5B, $20.9B, and $19.2B respectively."
      },
      {
        "heading": "?What do the top state totals show about overall obligations?",
        "body": "Top-state totals show the largest single-state obligations: Texas at $69.1B and Virginia at $64.2B. The top ten states listed together include amounts ranging from $69.1B down to $13.1B, within a total of $456B in obligations for FY2026 to date. The note clarifies that total award value figures are full contract values, not single-year obligations."
      }
    ]
  },
